  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-tender-closing-date field--type-datetime field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Closing Date&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Thu, 8 Sep. 2022&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;FACULTY OF SOCIAL SCIENCES - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;DEPARTMENT OF SOCIOLOGY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;FSS/S/TA 1/2022 - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;TEACHING ASSISTANT (2)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Successful&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt; candidates will work under the supervision of the Lecturers in conducting tutorials and achieving the Department’s teaching requirements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications should have a &lt;strong&gt;(i) &lt;/strong&gt;a Bachelor's degree in Sociology or combined Major Sociology, or Bachelor's degree in criminology/Criminal Justice with at least a 2&lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; pass; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; previous teaching experience, strong research methods background and/or Masters’ degree shall be an added advantage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;As per approved University of Botswana part time rates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;How &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; Apply: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants are to address the stated qualification and provide other information to assist the University determine their suitability for the position&lt;strong&gt;. &lt;/strong&gt;They should also quote the&lt;strong&gt; vacancy number of the post applied for, provide current CVs (including telephone, telefax and e-mail), certified copies of educational certificates and transcripts, samples of their publications, names and addresses of three referees, and send complete documentation to: The Human Resource Manager, Faculty of Social Sciences, Private Bag UB 00705, Gaborone-Botswana; Telephone: (267) 355 4894; Fax (267) 318 5099; E-mail: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:fssvacancies@ub.ac.bw"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;fssvacancies@ub.ac.bw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should inform their referees to: i) &lt;strong&gt;Quote the Vacancy number and position applied for&lt;/strong&gt; and ii) &lt;strong&gt;submit their references directly to the above address before the stipulated closing date. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;Please note that applications with incomplete information shall not be processed.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hand delivered applications should be submitted to Block 240, Office No. 137: (240/137). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;N&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;B: Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date:  8 September 2022&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
